question_title: Will the interest in “charles victor thompson” change between 2026-02-05 and 2026-02-12 according to Google Trends?
summary: Charles Victor Thompson was executed on January 28, 2026. Google Trends shows classic post-event decay: peak of 100 on Jan 29, now at ~1 on Feb 5. With the current value at the floor, "Decreases" is mathematically impossible (would require negative values). "Doesn't change" is highly likely as both Feb 5 and Feb 12 will be near 0-1. "Increases" would require unexpected news (documentary, death penalty debate, true crime coverage), which is possible but unlikely in a 7-day window.

factors.description: Current Feb 5 value is ~1, already at baseline floor - minimal room to decrease further
No upcoming events found - execution happened Jan 28, next Texas execution not until March
Mathematical constraint: 'Decreases' requires Feb 12 ≤ -3 when Feb 5 ≈ 1, which is impossible
Clear exponential decay pattern: 100 → 24 → 6 → 5 → 3 → 2 → 1 over 7 days
Small chance of unexpected news spike: documentary feature, death penalty debate, true crime coverage
